united states could best approach this new path of engagement the task force released its policy recommendation report in march 2010 with elections set to be held in burma on november 7 for the first time in 20 years the asia society has released a task force report update which provides an overview of key developments that have unfolded during recent months donald emmerson director of seaf is a member of the task force asia society current realities and future possibilities in burma myanmar original report and update search fsi search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages news of interest owens appointed to national task force february 16 2012 chp pcor fsi stanford news review us policy toward north korea robert carlin john w lewis washington post on november 22 2010 burma myanmar report conveys views of stanford scholars april 1 2010 shorenstein aparc seaf news seaf director named to task force on burma myanmar november 10 2009 shorenstein aparc seaf news protest and repression in burma myanmar what is to be done october 22 2007 shorenstein aparc seaf news john edwards what policy should the us pursue toward russia april 19 2006 press release support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 723 4581 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
